For example , they ’ ll make the main lead extra hard working and overly moral and make them unrealistically good . And they ’ ll make the villains unrealistically bad with all these traits . It makes the movie very shallow and boring for me cause most of them are this way . And the story won ’ t even be different . Same story , main lead has idea , some bad guys opposes , she does it anyways fails somehow and wants to give up , someone gives her a lecture to not give up , she does something and wins . and in between there ’ s some love story . This movie was geared to inspire women , so all these things will be about women empowerment somehow . Haven ’ t seen it but I bet even she gives a speech at the end about women . Similar to Srimanthudu / Maharishi , where Mahesh Babu is overly good and everything about the movie is geared towards giving back . If I remember he gives a speech I ’ m that too . That ’ s what I meant bro . Like , all these inspirational movie feel the same to me and feel routine and not entertaining and old format , and since this movie is specifically geared to inspire women that ’ s why I said that .
